==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intinction
<hw>In*tinc"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intinctio</ets>, fr. <ets>intingere</ets> to dip in; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>tingere</ets> to tinge.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of tingeing or dyeing.</def>
<rj><au>Blount.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A method or practice of the
administration of the sacrament by dipping the bread or wafer in the
wine and administering both together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intinctivity</ent>⟦br⟧
